# MCP Feature Parity

When adding or changing Ace Code Search capabilities that agents should use (search modes, query syntax, filters, pairing, index discovery, read-only inspection):

1. Update the read-only MCP surface in the same change: `src/mcp/tools.ts`, `src/mcp/server.ts`, and any needed `session`/`discover` support.
2. Prefer reusing existing `SearchService` / `IndexService` APIs; keep MCP read-only (no indexing, registry writes, or watchers).
3. Extend `test/mcpTools.test.ts` for new tools, parameters, filters, or result fields.
4. Sync agent docs in the same change:
   - `.agents/skills/ace-code-search-mcp/SKILL.md`
   - `resources/skills/ace-code-search-mcp/SKILL.md` (must stay byte-identical to the canonical `.agents` copy)
   - Do not create IDE-specific `.github`, `.cursor`, or `.claude` project guidance; current supported clients share `.agents/skills`
   - `AGENTS.md` / `README_Dev.md` for MCP behavior notes
5. If a feature is UI-only or unsafe for agents, explicitly document that it is out of MCP scope instead of silently omitting it.

Do not ship panel/CLI search behavior that agents cannot discover through MCP without an intentional, documented exception.
